cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about a deep learning-based method for single image deraining, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture, which involves the use of residuals to guide deeper blocks, and applies supervision to all intermediate results. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on synthetic and real-world data, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
